description:
Al programa Versió RAC1 de RAC 1 van fer un exercici d'imaginació sobre el futur de Catalunya després del 9N. Van convidar a 3 guionistes i escriptors perquè donessin la seva versió. Tot plegat, res de l'altre món, un recull de disbarats amb més o menys gràcia. Per a passar l'estona ja va estar bé. El Sergi Belbel va venir a dir que Espanya situaria l'exèrcit a l'altra banda de l'Ebre i els catalans, des de l'altra riba, botarien (amb B) i de tant botar farien separar Catalunya d'Espanya que quedaria com una illa. El problema de la imaginació de Belbel és que tot el Montsià i la Terra Alta seguirien enganxats a Espanya i si fa no fa la meitat del Baix Ebre i la meitat de la Ribera d'Ebre. Suposem que en Belbel quan escriu un guió o una obra de teatre es documenta millor.

Tot i això és d'agrair que Belbel se'n recordés de les Terres de l'Ebre per a centrar l'acció de la seva història "post 9N".

description:
Tarra is an organic house song with Greek elements and an emphasis on the lute organ. It’s a melodic journey from Crete to Africa especially when you listen to the Kalimba and the percussion organs. The two producers (Starwalk & Alej Ch) joined forces for a beautiful result. The inspiration for the song came from an ancient city in the south of Crete named Tarra.
Tarra was the seaport to Elyros where the very famous temple of Apollo and a healing center used to be. There is a legend that says that God Apollo came to Samaria after having killed the Python in Delphi, in order to get purified by the great priest and healer Karmanor where he fell in love with the Minoan nymph Akkakalis. Dazzled by her beauty, he stayed in her arms long enough to be late for bringing the dawn of the coming day. It was the longest night ever known in the world.

description:
Notes (Not Lyrics):

Most Recent Build

So here's a track I did to get a feel for GarageBand (v8). I wanted to learn the application in and out, push the limits of it, and see what it can and cannot do. It's not a bad little program; it's not without its limitations for sure and it's somewhat buggy but what app isn't. I kind of enjoy working in it's environment.

Anyhow, the track . . . It's comprised completely from the in-box softsynths, percussive samples; and effects and processing/mixing; bitcrusher FTW! I like the structure although I haven't changed it since the first hour or so I spent on it. There are lots of little nuances I programed that I thought GB did pretty well with.

All in all, GB is not too shabby and the "choon" is pretty groovy; at risk of sounding stupid.
title: GarageBand Test Track v9

description: What can we expect from the Premier League for its restart, and who's our team of the season so far?
title: Crossbar Podcast Episode 11: Team of the season and the Premier League returns!!

description:
The team is back for Episode 10 of the Crossbar Podcast!!
In this episode we take a look at what measures will be in place so that leagues across Europe can complete their seasons; as they continue to discuss when they will restart.

We also look at how delayed finishes across Europe will impact player contracts and the transfer window.
title: Episode 10: Plans Are In Place For Football To Resume Across Europe, So When Will Football Return?

description: Welcome to Episode 9 of the Crossbar Podcast!! In this episode we take take a look at the possible implications of Manchester City's prospective two-year Champions League ban, and other ramifications that it could have against other clubs.
title: Episode 9: Manchester City appeals Champions League ban – What happens next?

description: Welcome to Episode 8 of the Crossbar Podcast!! In this episode we take a deep dive into what's happening at Barcelona as well as having a talk about Hakim Ziyech's move to Chelsea
title: Episode 8: What's Happened to Barcelona?

description:
In the wake of the attack on the home of Man United Chairman, Ed Woodward, we ask if this latest incident represents a larger shift towards more toxic fan culture. 

Also listen in for our regular wrap up of the latest transfers, and of course, Bish's Stat Bash.
title: Is football fan culture becoming more toxic?

description: Hello and welcome to episode 6 of the Crossbar Podcast! We're discussing what it's like to commentate a match, discussing the movement of the 2021 African Cup of Nations, the biggest January transfers and much more!!
title: The Crossbar Podcast Episode 6: What's it Like To Commentate a Match?

description: Hi everyone and welcome to the fifth episode of the Crossbar Podcast!! We're discussing the Chinese Premier League, the transfer of Erling Braut Håland to Borussia Dortmund and far more!!
title: Crossbar Podcast - Episode 5

description:
Hello and welcome to the 
Crossbar Podcast!!

In this episode, we'll discuss Australia and New Zealand's joint bid for the women's world cup, the Champions League round of 16 draw and much more!!
title: The Crossbar Podcast – Episode 4- Will The 2023 Women's World Cup Be In Australia

description:
Welcome to episode three of the Transfer Podcast!

We're joined by special guest Jess Dunne to discuss our teams of the decade, Lionel Messi winning the Ballon D'or and much more!
title: The Crossbar Podcast – Episode 3

description:
Welcome to the second episode of the Crossbar Podcast with special guest Tim Fernandez for another dose of football analysis and discussion.

We'll be discussing the appointment of Jose Mourinho as Tottenham Hotspur manager and much more.
title: The Crossbar Podcast Episode 2

description:
Join Hugh Brassil, Max Gay and Bishoy Bassilious for another episode full of football news and debate.

In this week's podcast episode:
– Champions League Wrap
– Liverpool to play twice in 24 hours on two different continents
– Historic equal pay agreement for Australia's Socceroos & Matildas
– PREVIEW: Socceroos World Cup Qualifier against Jordan in Amman
title: The Crossbar Podcast – Episode 1
